  "body": "There's a mostly harmless but ugly shutdown phenomenon, when the tx pool is sometimes spewing out hundreds of error messages after the chain database has been closed and it still tries to create states and access trie nodes. It is caused by the protocol handler still trying to add transactions to the pool after closing the databases (and also after stopping both the pm and the tx pool).\n",
